Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.50,0:00:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Dr. David Hawkins. I've been a psychiatrist for 35 years, psychoanalyst, nutritionist,\Nresearcher into the nature of consciousness and spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.91,0:00:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this series of talks, we're using the knowledge that we gain from our research\Ninto the nature of consciousness itself for the alleviation of human suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.77,0:00:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's talk is addressed to letting go of weight,\Nhow to let go of weight in a way that's practical, easygoing, joyful,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.75,0:00:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and does not involve any kind of suffering.\NCan this be done?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.85,0:00:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, all we ask for is some of your attention,\Nmaybe an hour, hour and a half is all it's going to take of your attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.55,0:00:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,over a day or two, during a day which you're doing the other things that you would be doing anyway.\NThe benefits can be long-lasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.73,0:00:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They can last a long time.\NA lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.55,0:01:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The reward for a couple hours of just paying attention to a few simple principles\Nis a lifetime of freedom from this problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.80,0:01:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I know it works?\NBecause it's worked in everybody who's tried it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.54,0:01:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's worked in my patients.\NIt's worked in my own self.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.92,0:01:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I myself lost 50 pounds using this very simple technique\Ncoming out of our consciousness research.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.77,0:01:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The alleviation of a problem should be simple,\Ndirect,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.97,0:01:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to the point,\Nlong-lasting,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.27,0:01:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and its effect costs nothing.\NDiets not work and appetite suppressants will look into that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.01,0:01:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The usual techniques that people try\Nend up with sort of a guilty self-recrimination.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.53,0:01:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They work temporarily,\Nbut because they don't really change the way you are with your body,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.63,0:01:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because they don't really change those Pavlovian reflexes\Nwhich drive you into eating despite your best interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.25,0:02:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll talk about a shifting state of consciousness\Nthat we've discovered occurs in the process of eating itself
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.31,0:02:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and how you can easily overcome that\Nso that your weight loss becomes permanent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.84,0:02:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're going to say give up trying willpower,\Ngive up dieting,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.20,0:02:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,give up resisting eating as they don't work.\NThey make you miserable
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.90,0:02:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're going to end up the same as you were easier.\NAnyway, there's a much easier way that is truly joyful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.14,0:02:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be talking about,\Nand we'll be using during our talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.90,0:02:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,this scale of consciousness that we have over on the blackboard\Nthat we have been referring to in the other talks here in the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.24,0:02:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a mathematical model of levels of consciousness\Nas we commonly experience them in everyday life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.58,0:02:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And through our research,\Nwe were able to calibrate the relative energy power of these energy fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.28,0:03:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the directions of these energy fields,\Nand the importance that this has
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.78,0:03:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when we're trying to handle any kind of a human problem.\NAnd through a simple understanding of some very simple concepts,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.88,0:03:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we are then put in a place of being able to handle things\Nthat up to that time were baffling and not successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.32,0:03:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to talk about how to image yourself as slim\Nand love and energize that image
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.50,0:03:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and then let go of it so that it actually materializes.\NSo we're going to be using some of,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.40,0:03:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the techniques based upon the nature of consciousness itself.\NHow to come from your heart instead of your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.23,0:03:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How to come from your heart instead of your stomach.\NThe head criticizes you and the stomach wants to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.13,0:03:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only way to handle this problem\Nis to come from your heart about the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.09,0:03:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we're going to be somewhat lighthearted about this subject today,\Nin which many people get quite heavy about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.91,0:04:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The lightheartedness comes with the eating\Nand then the self-recrimination,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.17,0:04:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the self-recrimination,\Nand then the self-recrimination,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.33,0:04:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and the guilt comes, you know, as you go to bed,\Nyou lie in bed and you wonder,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.11,0:04:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,why did I eat all that?\NAnd begin to attack yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.04,0:04:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're going to find a way beyond all these problems\Nthat will work for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.60,0:04:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And so to start with, let's talk about,\Nlet's talk about the common medical model,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.04,0:04:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the one that is commonly tried.\NAnd we see that it's really based on the idea of diet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.20,0:04:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole concept is based on,\Nbased on an assumption that the number of calories you eat
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.40,0:04:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is what determines your weight,\Nplus maybe some thought to exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.01,0:04:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what we're going to say today\Nis not necessarily going to agree
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.71,0:04:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with traditional medical thinking.\NIf traditional medical thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.13,0:04:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and counting calories has worked for you,\Nyou wouldn't be watching this film.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.93,0:04:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're going to talk instead about things\Nthat we have clinically observed
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.89,0:05:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,as being true experientially.\NYou see, consciousness work has to be done
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.63,0:05:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,with the truth of one's own inner experience.\NIt does not have anything to do with theory
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.49,0:05:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,or a hypothesis or scientific reasoning or logic.\NIt has to do with the experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.99,0:05:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of the truth within you.\NSo the first thing we want to do
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.99,0:05:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is to begin to cancel some of our beliefs\Nabout diet and food that have contributed to our problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.88,0:05:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,To begin with, we have thoughts coming such as,\Nwell, overweight,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.72,0:05:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it runs in our family,\Nit's in the genes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.56,0:05:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it's due to my thyroid,\Nit's due to the fact that as an infant I was overweight
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.90,0:05:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and that caused too many fat cells.\NNow these are all popular medical theories
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and if holding those in mind works for you,\Nthen that is very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.82,0:05:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have found experientially\Nthis really isn't so, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.70,0:06:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because two people will eat exactly the same diet\Nand I've experienced this myself
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.10,0:06:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,over the last several years,\Nwhere myself and another person would eat
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.82,0:06:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,practically the same number of calories.\NOne would gain weight and the other would lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.78,0:06:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So how do you explain that phenomenon\Nin as much as the activity levels are about the same
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.48,0:06:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything else is about the same?\NSo we have to question some of the basic medical hypothesis
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.55,0:06:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see that some of them are very simple to understand.\NTo begin with, why assume because you eat 100 calories
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.70,0:06:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that the body therefore absorbs 100 calories?\NWhat makes you think that two people,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.64,0:06:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the two people's gastrointestinal tract are exactly the same?\NI ate a 1,000 calorie piece of pie
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.40,0:06:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and another person eats a 1,000 calorie piece of pie.\NMaybe I only absorb 500 calories out of that 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.50,0:06:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The other 500 runs right on through.\NAnd so we have other factors such as the rate of movement
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.57,0:06:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of the gastrointestinal tract.\NWe know that the faster things move through the tract,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.87,0:07:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the less things are absorbed.\NSo we have other factors to consider
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.17,0:07:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,than just calories.\NAnd so we're going to talk about these things today
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.21,0:07:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and arrive at a way of handling this problem\Nthat will not involve counting calories.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.84,0:07:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some dietary tricks that are helpful\Nand so we'll throw in some tricks about eating
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.78,0:07:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that are helpful in the beginning until the results\Nof your working on yourself have adjusted your epistat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.48,0:07:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So today we're going to be talking about,\Na portion of the brain in the hypothalamus,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.08,0:07:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which is called the epistat and how to set down your epistat.\NIt takes you a day or two to handle this problem
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.98,0:07:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the epistat gets reset.\NAnd because the epistat controls your feeling of satiety,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.88,0:08:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it will now control your weight and as you hold a certain weight\Nin mind, it begins to materialize on the physical plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.58,0:08:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll again be talking about the power of mind over body.\NThe power of mind over body and we'll be looking at the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.98,0:08:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is mind that creates body being what it is rather\Nthan the other way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.58,0:08:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to reverse the conventional so-called common sense\Nof the left brain logic which says it's the body
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.60,0:08:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that creates the mind.\NInstead we have to look at the opposite, that what is held
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.48,0:08:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in mind manifests within the body so that our thoughts\Nand our beliefs about weight, activity,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.88,0:08:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,calories and all the phenomena surrounding this have been\Nwhat is affecting our weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.04,0:08:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We know this from let's say cases of patients\Nwith multiple personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.30,0:08:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,One personality will come into the patient and take\Nover his consciousness named Dick.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.76,0:09:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Dick doesn't have any eating or weight problem at all.\NIn fact, he eats very little.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.99,0:09:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He's spry and active.\NAnd while Dick is in the body, the person is slim
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.67,0:09:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and loses weight.\NThen the person will go into a trance state
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.16,0:09:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,or become intoxicated or something.\NAnd Robert comes into the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.76,0:09:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Robert loves to eat.\NHe gorges himself on all kinds of things, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.94,0:09:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the person's weight suddenly rises dramatically.\NSo you see the response now of the body is therefore to the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.96,0:09:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to the mindset, to the mind's beliefs, to the mind's attitudes,\Nto the way the person holds their relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.30,0:09:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to their body in their mind.\NIt is the mind that is going to be setting our epistat
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.90,0:09:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and is using consciousness techniques within the mind\Nwhich are going to release our weight problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.30,0:09:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can let go of the weight almost automatically.\NI want to review again with you the nature
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.37,0:10:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself.\NThat relationship between body, mind and spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.27,0:10:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirit being that energy field of consciousness\Nwhich is all pervasive throughout life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.30,0:10:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing to understand is that the body has no capacity\Nto experience itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,At first this seems like an amazing thought.\NBecause most of us, unless we're enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.73,0:10:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,assume that we are the physical body.\NThe first thing to realize is that the body has no way
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.18,0:10:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in which to experience itself.\NMy arm cannot experience my arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.48,0:10:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,My leg cannot experience my leg.\NInstead it has to be experiencing something greater
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.59,0:10:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,than itself.\NAnd so we experience the body via the senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.09,0:10:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the senses that tell us what is going on with the body.\NSo we're not experiencing the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.35,0:10:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We're experiencing the senses of the body.\NNow the senses of the body themselves have no capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.31,0:11:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience themselves.\NThey have to be experienced in something greater
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.31,0:11:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,than what they are and that is mind itself.\NSo we have the mind is the place
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.28,0:11:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the body is.\NThe body is experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.54,0:11:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In which the sensations from the body are experienced.\NMind itself is incapable of experiencing itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.80,0:11:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this seems like an amazing thought also, isn't it?\NA thought cannot experience its own thoughtness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.94,0:11:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,A memory cannot experience its own memoryness.\NA fantasy of the future cannot experience itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.74,0:11:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,An emotion cannot experience itself.\NWhat goes on in the mind has to be experienced in something
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.32,0:11:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which itself cannot experience.\NMind itself is greater than mind, and that is consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.10,0:11:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have the body is experienced via sensation.\NSensation is experienced in the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.22,0:11:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind is experienced in consciousness.\NWe can see this very easily because if something happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.02,0:12:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say to a portion of the brain,\Nwe know that the person is unable to experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.68,0:12:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say the opposite side of the body.\NSo without mind, body cannot be experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.33,0:12:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We know.\NWe know because of anesthesia, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.26,0:12:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, that is the whole point of anesthesia.\NThat without consciousness, we're not aware of what is going on in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.42,0:12:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If you delete consciousness via the anesthetic,\Nthere is no knowledge or experience now of what is going on in either mind or body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.46,0:12:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness is higher than mind and body.\NThere is, in fact, a state beyond consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.28,0:12:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which is still and unmoving, against which,\Nwe are then aware of what is going on in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.04,0:12:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the state of awareness.\NThe state of awareness, which is not different
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.54,0:12:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,than the great powerful energy field behind consciousness itself,\Nwhich is not different than the energy of life itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.94,0:13:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which is not different than one's godness,\Nif these are terms that are acceptable to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.84,0:13:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It is necessary to know this because we then become aware of where all experience is taking place.\NThe experience is taking place within consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.96,0:13:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All human experience is taking place in consciousness itself.\NConsequently, I cannot experience the wall or the floor or you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.66,0:13:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm experiencing is within my own consciousness of you or the wall or the floor.\NThis gives us an understanding of an area in which we can work then,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.41,0:13:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,which is less restricted by consciousness,\Nwhich is less restricted by the commonly held belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.41,0:13:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If the entire weight problem is a phenomena occurring within consciousness itself,\Nif consciousness is more powerful than mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.41,0:13:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which is more powerful than senses,\Nwhich is more powerful than body,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.48,0:14:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then we can bring about a shift in the body by merely addressing consciousness itself.\NIf we address the problem there,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.48,0:14:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because the body will only do what is held in mind,\Nwe don't have to really bother much with the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.48,0:14:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The body will automatically correct itself\Nbecause the problem is really a problem within the experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.48,0:14:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,within consciousness itself.\NSo we'll be addressing techniques which have to do with the mind and with consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.48,0:14:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and we won't have to be very much concerned then with handling the body as such.\NYou might say that the body is an effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.60,0:14:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The cause is in mind.\NThe cause of what happens in the body is in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.60,0:14:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only an effect.\NConsequently, the attempts to solve the weight problem
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.60,0:14:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which are addressed to the body only are notoriously unsuccessful.\NPractically every month you see endless magazines and newspapers
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.02,0:15:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and the headline on the cover which sells them is a new diet.\NThis tells you that diets don't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.63,0:15:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When you find multiple solutions to a problem,\Nwhen there are endless articles on the same phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.95,0:15:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you know they don't have the answer.\NIf you had the answer to the weight problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.95,0:15:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,there wouldn't be any articles on diet at all\Nbecause everybody would have handled it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.95,0:15:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Addressing it on the physical level alone just doesn't work.\NIt just doesn't work for many other problems
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.95,0:15:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,which involve complicated human behavior,\Nsuch problems as alcoholism,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.95,0:15:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,many illnesses including duodenal ulcers, etc., diverticulitis.\NAll these things are notoriously non-responsive
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.95,0:15:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to addressing them on the physical level only.\NWe have to become more sophisticated and more conscious ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.98,0:15:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring about a resolution of long-standing behavioral problems.\NThe technique which I used personally when I lost that 50 pounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.98,0:16:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which may not sound like a lot of pounds to some of you,\Nbut it was 30% of my body weight because at the time I weighed 175,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.98,0:16:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and with this technique I went down to 125,\Nwhich was the weight that I desired.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.98,0:16:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This technique really only worked\Nbecause it only takes, as I had promised you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.52,0:16:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,really a matter of minutes over a day or two.\NCollectively, we're asking for maybe an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.52,0:16:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,an hour and a half of your time and attention.\NYou can actually do this while you're going about the house
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.52,0:16:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or going about in the office, driving back and forth to work.\NYou can just fit it into your daily routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.52,0:16:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't something that you really have to stop your life in order to handle.\NIt isn't like going away to a milk farm
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.59,0:16:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,or going to a dance studio or something.\NThis is something that works right into your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.84,0:16:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,For a thing to be effective, it has to fit in with your life pattern.\NI found that any behavioral modification technique
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.84,0:16:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,works if it fits in with your daily life.\NIf you have to change your whole lifestyle,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.84,0:17:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,then usually the results are temporary.\NIn this case, what we do is when the sensation comes on
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.97,0:17:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have previously called hunger,\Nwhat you do is you ignore the thoughts that go with this,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.97,0:17:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,especially canceling that thought, hunger,\Nand instead you go right into the sensations,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.97,0:17:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,right into the inner experience\Nof what it is you're actually experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.97,0:17:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and where you're experiencing it in your body\Nwithout labeling it, without calling it anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.97,0:17:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,without putting any name on it,\Nto just experience it and begin to let go,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.97,0:17:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,resisting those sensations.\NWe go into consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.10,0:17:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We go into the inner experience\Nof what you're experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.10,0:17:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,without labeling it with anything,\Nwithout calling it anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.10,0:17:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, to silently go within\Nand experience what's being experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.10,0:17:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and let go, resisting it.\NIn the beginning, you are so controlled
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.48,0:18:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,by the Pavlovian conditioning\Nthat the minute you get this sensation,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.48,0:18:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the behavior goes into immediate action to satisfy it.\NAnd so, like Pavlov's dog who ate,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.48,0:18:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, salivated every time the bell rang,\Nwhat you've done is set up a conditioned reflex
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.48,0:18:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and what we want to do is unset this.\NHow can we unset it and how long does this take?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.96,0:18:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How much effort?\NVery little effort, very little time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.99,0:18:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What we do instead is when we get this sensation,\Nwhich in the past we've called hungry,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.99,0:18:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm hungry now,\Nwhat we do is we let go, resisting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.99,0:18:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We just agree and we're willing to be with the sensation\Nbut do nothing about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.08,0:18:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So I let the experience\Nrun within me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.08,0:18:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm willing to be with that inner experience\Nof whatever it is, the sensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.24,0:18:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people may sense it in the stomach.\NSome people may sense it in sort of a physical weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.31,0:19:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever the sensation is,\Nwe stop talking about it in our mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.31,0:19:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We stop languaging it.\NWe stop giving it a label.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.31,0:19:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, we go into the inner experience\Nand we let go, resisting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.85,0:19:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In letting go, resisting it,\Nwe can move up to a higher energy level
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.85,0:19:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,if we choose it, if we're willing,\Nif we say to ourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.85,0:19:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I want more of whatever that is.\NNow the reason for that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.85,0:19:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and the way that it will make it acceptable to you\Nis that there is a limited amount
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.85,0:19:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of this sensation that's coming up.\NThe mind thinks, if I don't satisfy this,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.24,0:19:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to be beset by this hungry feeling continuously.\NThat's not so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.24,0:19:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That is coming from resisting it.\NWhen we go with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.40,0:19:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,like in the Tao,\Nyou know, the Chinese philosophy,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.40,0:19:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,where the willow tree bends with the wind\Nand therefore doesn't break,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.40,0:19:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as compared to the oak tree,\Nwhich resists the wind and of course is broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.62,0:19:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of being the oak tree\Nwho resists this sensation
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.62,0:20:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and tries to battle it with willpower\Nand fight it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.62,0:20:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we're like the willow tree.\NWe go with the sensation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.62,0:20:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and we let go, resisting it.\NIn fact, we will resist it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.81,0:20:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, we welcome it.\NIt's like we're saying more.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.81,0:20:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We want more wind.\NWe want more of this inner experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.81,0:20:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As we call forth more of it,\Nwe like empty it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.81,0:20:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I sit with this inner feeling now\Nand I let it be with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.81,0:20:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I can actually stop,\Nif I'm doing this at home
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.70,0:20:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and I suggest you start it at a weekend when you're home,\NI can even stop everything
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.92,0:20:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and really focus on that.\NI don't want anything to distract
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.92,0:20:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,from my being with this sensation\Nand as I sit with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.05,0:20:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in a matter of minutes,\Nit will suddenly disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.05,0:20:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,After it disappears,\NI can go about my business
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.17,0:20:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and after you become used to this technique,\Nyou don't have to stop your activities at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.17,0:20:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When that experience comes up,\Nyou fix and focus on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.20,0:21:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You concentrate on it.\NYou fix your attention on your welcoming it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.20,0:21:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're opening the barn door\Nand allowing that to come into you willingly,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.20,0:21:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,being with that sensation\Nbut not doing anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.20,0:21:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to break that cycle\Nwhere you get that sensation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.20,0:21:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which your mind then labels hunger,\Nyou then satisfy it with food
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.20,0:21:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and what you've just done is reinforce,\Nmade yourself victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.20,0:21:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,made yourself at the effect of that behavior pattern.\NInstead, that which you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.16,0:21:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,your person, yourself,\Nstands aside from this sensation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.16,0:21:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and begins to master it\Nso that you're no longer at the effect of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.32,0:21:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you are the master.\NYou know, in Zen,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.55,0:21:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,they have the famous ox herding pictures.\NAnd in the first picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.55,0:21:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it shows the monk\Nand he's hanging on to this rope
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.55,0:21:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is attached to the ox\Nand the ox is dragging him all across the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.55,0:21:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,\Nand his knees are bruised
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.55,0:21:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's bleeding from his ears\Nand he's all a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.55,0:22:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you see the next picture,\Nhe has the ox
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.55,0:22:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's got this ox,\Nthe rope tied to a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.55,0:22:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,\Nnow he has caught the ox,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.55,0:22:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,he has identified what the problem is.\NAnd then the next picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.55,0:22:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you see him,\Nhe's riding on top of the ox.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.55,0:22:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He has become the master.\NHe's no longer the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.55,0:22:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,he's no longer at the effect of it.\NAnd how did he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.77,0:22:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He did it just,\Nthat's what we're doing right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.77,0:22:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to tether this ox right now\Nby identifying what is the pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.77,0:22:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that has to be handled\Nand then we're going to be on top of it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.77,0:22:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the person that we are now\Nstands independent above and beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.77,0:22:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and becomes the master of this.\NVery simple thing to solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.77,0:22:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very simple,\Nit's merely the willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.25,0:22:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience what in the beginning\Nmay seem like some discomfort.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.25,0:22:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,\Nto experience this sensation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.25,0:22:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,without satiating it right away.\NAs we do this,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.12,0:23:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we weaken the reflex.\NWell, what about our eating during the day?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.12,0:23:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do about that?\NWell, what we do about our eating
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.12,0:23:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is what I call anticipatory eating.\NYou never eat when you're hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.12,0:23:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The first two days that you do this,\Nand in fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.12,0:23:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,probably for the first week or two,\Nnever allow yourself to eat when you're hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.12,0:23:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead,\Nyou let go of this hungriness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.12,0:23:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,by using this radical truth technique.\NAnd what you do is you anticipate
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.69,0:23:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,periods of hunger.\NYou know your own hunger patterns.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.79,0:23:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of waiting until you're hungry\Nand eating,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.79,0:23:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which reinforces the pattern,\Ninstead you anticipate.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.79,0:23:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that habitually\Nyou're going to be hungry around 6 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.79,0:23:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you do,\Ninstead of waiting until you're hungry
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.79,0:23:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and then satisfying it,\Nthereby reinforcing your own conditioning,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.79,0:23:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,what you do is you anticipate it\Nbefore you're hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.79,0:23:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Quarter to five,\Nyou're not even hungry yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.92,0:23:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Quarter to five,\Nyou have a cheese sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.17,0:24:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're not hungry.\NSo the technique is simple then.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.36,0:24:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You eat when you're not hungry\Nand you don't eat when you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.36,0:24:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead,\Nyou substitute this technique
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.36,0:24:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for the hunger pattern.\NNow, how long will this take
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.36,0:24:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,before you disappear hunger?\NWhat is going to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.46,0:24:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen\Nis that you will no longer experience hunger.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.62,0:24:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You will no longer experience appetite.\NIt will seem to disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.62,0:24:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,By the second day,\Nyou'll notice that it is already so weak
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.62,0:24:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that you barely notice it.\NHow many minutes a day will this take?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.62,0:24:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The first day,\Nmaybe a total of half an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.62,0:24:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that\Nif you do nothing about this sensation
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.62,0:24:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and really let go resisting it,\Nthat it will disappear
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.62,0:24:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in a matter of minutes.\NAfter you do this a number of times,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.62,0:24:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it will disappear in a matter of seconds.\NYou'll know that if you sit down
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.62,0:24:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and let go resisting this sensation,\Nthat in seconds it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.62,0:24:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In seconds,\Nyou're no longer at the effect of this appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.62,0:25:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You're no longer driven by it.\NYou can be absolutely free of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.32,0:25:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In place of this pattern then,\Nyou may feel instead sort of a blankness,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.21,0:25:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of an emptiness,\Nlike where there once was this hunger
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.31,0:25:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and the drive to eat,\Nand then the appetite,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.31,0:25:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the enthusiasm about it,\Nand then the satiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.56,0:25:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like nothing is going on\Nin that space in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.56,0:25:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you can do instead\Nis do some other pleasurable activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.76,0:25:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Do some other pleasurable activity.\NReward yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.76,0:25:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The book that you've been wanting to read\Nand have never had the time to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.76,0:25:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now that you're not out in the kitchen all the time,\Neating all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.76,0:25:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll have some time to read that novel,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.76,0:25:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the one that you just want to read for enjoyment,\Nand you feel too guilty to read it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.76,0:25:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because you really have more important things to do.\NThe trashy magazine that you've been wanting to read all week,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.82,0:25:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but you feel too guilty to give the time to it.\NWell, get yourself something that you really enjoy doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.82,0:26:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing I like to do, for instance,\Nis take a nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.82,0:26:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All the time you spend eating food,\Nand preparing food,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.82,0:26:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and cleaning up from the food,\Nand shopping the food,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.82,0:26:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Ncan take up a great part of your day.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.04,0:26:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives you time for a short nap.\NIt really feels great.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.04,0:26:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,After a 20-minute nap,\Nyou feel fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.04,0:26:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,After a 20-minute hunger engorgement,\Nyou know that you don't feel fantastic,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.11,0:26:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you feel horrible.\NYou just had four Milky Ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.11,0:26:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,a caramel sundae,\Nand finished off a piece of cheese,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.11,0:26:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and now,\Ninstead of feeling happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.11,0:26:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you're feeling guilty.\NThe way off the guilt trip, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.59,0:26:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is to really know that there is a very simple technique.\NIt sounds so simple,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.59,0:26:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's why it works.\NYou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.59,0:26:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,things that are extraordinarily complicated\Nare usually far from the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.59,0:26:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is usually amazingly simple.\NAs people, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.59,0:26:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in Alcoholics Anonymous have found out,\Nstay away from one drink one day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.59,0:26:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds so simple.\NThe intellect says,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.59,0:26:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,nonsensical,\NI know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.59,0:26:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You know it.\NThe intellect knows it,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.75,0:26:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but you,\Nyour person,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.75,0:27:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't know that.\NWe only know a thing through our own validation,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.75,0:27:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,through our own inner experience.\NWithin a day or two,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.26,0:27:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it usually takes me exactly one day\Nto get off eating,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.26,0:27:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and hunger,\Nand appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.26,0:27:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've allowed yourself to get reprogrammed,\Nyou'll notice as time goes on,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.26,0:27:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you're beginning to look forward to meals,\Nyou're starting to get into the habit pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.26,0:27:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of getting hungry and satisfying it.\NIt's very simple to get back off it,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.26,0:27:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to release yourself back off of it,\Nby doing this just a few times.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.26,0:27:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so effective with me now\Nthat I can do it just once.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.26,0:27:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All I have to do\Nis allow that feeling of hungriness to come up,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.26,0:27:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,just be with it,\Nwelcome it,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.26,0:27:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,wait until it runs out,\Nand that handles it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.26,0:27:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe every few years\NI have to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.26,0:27:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'll have to do that\Nif I've really gotten into holiday indulgence
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.26,0:27:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for a number of years.\NBecause another thing that goes on is,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.64,0:27:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as we do this,\Nthere is a center in the base of the brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.64,0:27:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in the hypothalamus,\Ncalled the apostat.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.64,0:28:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostat sets our degree of satiety,\Nthe amount of satiety that we are searching for.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.64,0:28:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the less we eat,\Nthe more we set down our apostat.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.64,0:28:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, talking about satiety,\Nyou see,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.06,0:28:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's something else\Nthat is not really understood
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.06,0:28:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in traditional scientific medicine.\NScientific medicine talks about calories,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.06,0:28:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as though one calorie was the same as another calorie.\NBut we all know
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.06,0:28:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that satiety plays a great place\Nin our hunger and our weight problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.09,0:28:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Satiety is more important than calories.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.09,0:28:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the diet I follow\Nwould make most people who follow diets faint.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.12,0:28:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know\Nwhat creates a feeling of satiety
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.12,0:28:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,within myself.\NCertain types of things,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.44,0:28:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,like a hamburger smothered in onions.\NBy the time you finish that,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.44,0:28:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you get that totally filled up,\Nsatisfied,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.44,0:28:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nmeat and cheese
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.44,0:28:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and those kind of foods.\NCheese is not on,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.53,0:29:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nanybody's reducing diet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.53,0:29:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But we know that cheese has quite a,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.53,0:29:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,satiety factor.\NSo that once you've eaten a certain amount of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.60,0:29:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like your appetite is satisfied.\NWe also know that calories are released
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.60,0:29:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,at different rates.\NAnd so that fats,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.60,0:29:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,for once,\Nfor instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.60,0:29:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,are released at one rate,\Nprotein at another.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.69,0:29:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that it takes a lot of calories,\Na number of calories,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.69,0:29:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to burn up every gram of protein.\NSo one of the tricks,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.04,0:29:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of course,\Nwhich you can use
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.04,0:29:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to speed up the process\Nof the weight loss with yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.04,0:29:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is to go in for a heavily,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.04,0:29:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,high protein diet.\NWe know that some foods,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.40,0:29:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we're not going to be talking about diet today,\Nbut I'll just throw in a few tricks
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.40,0:29:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that I've observed clinically\Nand I know work.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.75,0:29:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That eating sugar on an empty stomach\Nis sort of deleterious to the goals of your program.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.75,0:29:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause the body takes it in so fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.75,0:30:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it's absorbed so rapidly,\Nit can't be metabolized that fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.75,0:30:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and it just has to be stored within the body.\NSo one thing we do for our own sake then,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.75,0:30:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because part of this is caring for ourself,\Nloving ourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.75,0:30:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is to try and avoid sugar and sweets\Nwhen we're introducing this program into our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.75,0:30:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Downstream, you can eat them.\NI eat hot fudge sundaes all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.75,0:30:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and I love chocolate fudge,\Nand anything chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.13,0:30:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So I haven't found at this point in my life\Nthat eating those things has any effect on weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.13,0:30:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the beginning,\Nbecause you want to see a fast result,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.13,0:30:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and I believe you should,\NI believe you should have the satisfaction
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.13,0:30:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of doing this thing now\Nand seeing some return, some reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.68,0:30:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing the image that you've been holding of yourself\Ncome into manifestation.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.19,0:31:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably best to avoid\Nthings that are heavily sugar,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.19,0:31:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,especially on an empty stomach.\NSo our technique then is to let go resisting
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.51,0:31:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and to disappear hunger and appetite.\NYou then live in a world
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.51,0:31:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,where you're no longer in the cycle,\Nyou see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.51,0:31:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You get used to an eating cycle\Nof overeating,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.54,0:31:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling guilty about the overeating,\Nthen trying to control it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.54,0:31:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then up comes hunger.\NWith the hunger comes guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.47,0:31:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,With it comes appetite.\NWith it comes the expectation of satiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.47,0:31:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then comes the overindulgence.\NThen comes the guilt again.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.47,0:31:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have this endless self-defeating cycle.\NThe only way to beat it is to rise above it,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.56,0:31:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend it,\Nto be beyond it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.56,0:31:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And by disappearing,\Nyou'll find that appetite and hunger
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.79,0:31:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,actually disappears.\NAnd you'll have the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.79,0:31:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of never being hungry.\NWell, the next thing the mind says,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.79,0:31:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to give up the pleasure of eating.\NSounds like you're going to come into a loss, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.79,0:31:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to be able to enjoy\Na molten milk or a hot fed sundae
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.79,0:32:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,or a hamburger smothered in onions.\NQuite the contrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.79,0:32:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens to the enjoyment of eating\Nonce you do this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.79,0:32:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is that appetite arises out of the eating itself.\NSo I'll sit down with no hunger
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.14,0:32:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and no appetite at all.\NBut the minute I begin to eat,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.14,0:32:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it creates appetite.\NAnd the pleasure of eating
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.14,0:32:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is more than it ever was.\NI enjoy food now more than I ever did.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.36,0:32:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's why it's not accompanied by guilt anymore.\NIt's not accompanied by self-blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.36,0:32:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not accompanied by anxiety.\NAm I eating too many calories?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.36,0:32:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I going to gain weight from this?\NAll that's eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.68,0:32:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're not going to give up\Nthe pleasure of eating at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.68,0:32:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll find that when you eat\Nwhen you're not hungry,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.68,0:32:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're enjoying the food considerably.\NWhen do you start enjoying the cheese sandwich?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.94,0:32:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you take a bite into it.\NNot even hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.94,0:32:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I pick up the cheese sandwich.\NI bite into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.94,0:33:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The enjoyment is there.\NThere's no loss of enjoyment.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.09,0:33:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe in letting go enjoyment and pleasure.\NOn the contrary,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.09,0:33:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in increasing it.\NSo now you'll have the enjoyment
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.09,0:33:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and the pleasure of eating\Nas well as the enjoyment and pleasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.09,0:33:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and the justified pride\Nin having a body that's more appropriate
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.09,0:33:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to your own aesthetic ambitions.\NAnd we'll be talking about that next,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.19,0:33:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,your own aesthetic ambitions\Nas to what you would like to look like
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.19,0:33:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and a technique perhaps\Nthat will help bring that into manifestation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.19,0:33:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we need the actual handling\Nof that cycle of eating, getting hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.80,0:33:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see what's happening.\NYou see that you are the victim
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.80,0:33:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of a behavioral pattern, a conditioning.\NIt has nothing to do with willpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.80,0:33:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with morality.\NYou see, we can condition any kind of an animal in this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.80,0:34:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happened is sort of a Pavlovian dog conditioning,\Nand it has nothing really to do with your personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.80,0:34:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with your self-worth.\NIt has nothing to do with the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.80,0:34:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're self-indulgent.\NIt has nothing to do with oral narcissistic needs
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.80,0:34:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever the psychoanalytic theory might be,\Noral aggression, oral passivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.80,0:34:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got nothing to do with that, you see.\NIt merely has to do with a simple,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.66,0:34:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,very primary type of conditioning\Nwhich has been favored in our society.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.66,0:34:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You picked it up from your own social conditioning\Nas a child, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.66,0:34:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll be talking about the child\Nand the part that the child plays.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.66,0:34:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And moving on now,\Nto a different way of looking at the whole eating pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.66,0:34:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind, the body is experienced in mind,\Nand the mind is experienced in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.76,0:34:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So where you're really experiencing\Nthat which you've called hunger in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.76,0:34:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is in your consciousness.\NAnd where is that localized?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.82,0:35:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that it's only a belief system\Nthat it's experienced in the stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.82,0:35:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's actually experienced\Nin sort of a generalized way
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.82,0:35:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in sort of everywhere.\NThe thought that it is in the stomach,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.08,0:35:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is just a belief system from childhood.\NAs we said before,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.08,0:35:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the body cannot experience anything.\NWhat is going on is experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.08,0:35:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in a more diffuse, generalized area.\NSo another trick, another technique
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.30,0:35:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in letting go of suffering of any kind,\Nwhether it's pain or illness or physical symptoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.30,0:35:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in this case, what we've been calling hunger,\Nis nothing but a physical symptom.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.49,0:35:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that it is being experienced\Nin a general, diffuse kind of way.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.49,0:35:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's being experienced sort of everywhere.\NBecause where do we experience all experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.49,0:35:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's being experienced\Nin an everywhere-ness,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.49,0:35:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than a localized situation.\NThe localization is coming from
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.49,0:36:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the strong belief systems.\NYou know, we have all these thoughts from childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.84,0:36:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,As we let go, resisting this energy\Nof this sensation,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.84,0:36:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes diffuse and finally it disappears.\NWell, this is very interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.84,0:36:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because we'll go over to the board now.\NWe'll go to this map of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.84,0:36:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this mathematical model,\Nand see if we can get some kind of sense out of it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.84,0:36:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint of energy fields.\NHere we have the levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.09,0:36:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,these energy fields starting at the bottom,\Nthe lower feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.09,0:36:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And we notice as we come up here\Nto desire,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.09,0:36:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,which is what has been running us\Nwith our appetite-hunger satiation cycle,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.09,0:36:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we notice that it has an energy field\Nthat's been calibrated at 125.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.09,0:36:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We notice that the direction of the energy field\Nis in a negative direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.09,0:37:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, it has a deleterious effect on our life.\NAnd we notice that the emotion
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.09,0:37:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that goes with this energy field\Nis wanting and craving,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.09,0:37:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the addictions then fall into this.\NSo calling a weight problem a food addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.09,0:37:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way is correct\Nin that we're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.09,0:37:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,this particular energy field right here.\NAnd we see what is characteristic
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.09,0:37:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of this negative 125 energy field\Nis a feeling of wantingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.09,0:37:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,desiringness, cravingness.\NAnd we see that the process going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.09,0:37:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the process going on in consciousness\Nis entrapment.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.67,0:37:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The person therefore feels like this,\Nlike a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.67,0:37:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And because of the direction\Nof the energy field here,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.67,0:37:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there are negative feelings about the self\Nhaving to do with this whole cycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.76,0:37:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As we let go resisting it\Nand get released off of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.76,0:38:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,go beyond it,\Nyou see what's happening now
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.76,0:38:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is we start moving up to the courage\Nto handle this problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.76,0:38:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the pride and our willingness to look at it.\NAnd we move up,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.76,0:38:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we make it off this cycle\Nand to this level here
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.76,0:38:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a plus 250\Nin which we become unattached, detached.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.83,0:38:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that point the phenomena,\Nthe process going on in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.83,0:38:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you're released.\NBecause the energy field now goes to the right,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.31,0:38:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a positive good feeling.\NIt's constructive
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.31,0:38:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and it makes us feel better.\NIt has a lot of power in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.31,0:38:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do we experience that detachment?\NIt's an experience that,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.01,0:38:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,well, if we eat it's okay\Nand if I don't eat it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.01,0:38:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, you want to eat something now?\NI say, well, if you're going to fix something, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.01,0:38:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you know, they'll say,\Nwell, what do you want to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.08,0:38:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to eat this?\NDo you want macaroni
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.08,0:39:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or do you want baked beans?\NAnd you say, well, either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.08,0:39:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when you reach this level\Nof handling appetite and hunger,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.08,0:39:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you're no longer really fixed\Non one particular food or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.08,0:39:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say, well,\Nif we have a steak tonight, that's fine
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.14,0:39:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and if we don't, that's fine.\NSo it's okay either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.14,0:39:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It means you're free, you see.\NAnd one characteristic is freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.14,0:39:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom from what?\NFreedom from being run by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.14,0:39:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom from being a victim of that.\NFreedom from the entrapment
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.17,0:39:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which made us feel bad about ourself.\NThe negative energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.17,0:39:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,makes us feel bad about ourself.\NSo automatically,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.17,0:39:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,as we get detached from these sensations,\Nwe begin to feel good about ourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.17,0:39:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, our willingness to do that\Nmoves us up to 310,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.17,0:39:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which is an even better feeling about it.\NWe begin to accept
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.17,0:40:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is nothing but a phenomena.\NYou see, it's just a set of vibrations
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.17,0:40:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,going on within consciousness.\NIt doesn't have to do with food.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.17,0:40:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to do with the body.\NThose are all programs.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.17,0:40:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In essence, the physics of it is\Nthat it's just a set of vibrations
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.17,0:40:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,going on in the field of consciousness\Nwhich are within our power to alter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.17,0:40:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And once we do that,\Nwe can really begin to love ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.17,0:40:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,more than we did before.\NThere's another aspect going on in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.25,0:40:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that's very interesting\Nthat will be very helpful to you also.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.25,0:40:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Something you can observe within yourself.\NSomething I picked up within myself
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.25,0:40:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and saw it happening.\NYou see, the cycle in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.80,0:40:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,has been to be run by this hunger, appetite,\Nsatiation, and then guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.80,0:40:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is,\Nyour good intentions suddenly flew out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.80,0:41:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The good intentions that you had about\Ntaking off weight and dieting and all that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.80,0:41:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,have disappeared somewhere.\NAnd after you have filled yourself up
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.89,0:41:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with far more than you knew you needed,\Nsuddenly you go into a feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.89,0:41:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of this self-disgust and guilt.\NAnd people who have severe eating problems
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.89,0:41:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,often do that.\NThey go in the bathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.99,0:41:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and throw all the food back up again\Nand they go into self-hatred and guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.99,0:41:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and even suicidal depressions.\NThe self-hatred becomes severe, the blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.05,0:41:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is going on here?\NWell, what I saw happening was
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.47,0:41:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,when you sit down to eat,\Nyou see, the one who wants to take off weight
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.47,0:41:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and all this is the adult in us.\NRemember Eric Berne,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.47,0:41:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the transactional analysis?\NA lot of people in that kind of psychological work
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.50,0:41:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,have talked about our child tape,\Nour adult tape, and our parent tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.50,0:42:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It is like there are three voices within us.\NOne is the child,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.50,0:42:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,one is the adult,\Nwho is the rational, intelligent, educated person,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.50,0:42:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and one is the parent,\Nwho tends to be punitive,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.50,0:42:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,who tends to be moralistic.\NThe parent tape is the one that tells you about right and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.50,0:42:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you will see that this is what has been happening.\NAs you sit down to the table
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.88,0:42:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or as you walk into the refrigerator,\Nyou go unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.88,0:42:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You go unconscious and what happens is\Nthe child takes over.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.36,0:42:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what does the child know about diet, weight, calories?\NNothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.36,0:42:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness of the child is\NI want and I satisfy, I get.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.36,0:42:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what happens is\Nwe go into, without realizing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.36,0:42:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a different state of consciousness\Nin which the child is really...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.36,0:42:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, who is in the refrigerator poking around?\NThe child is.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.61,0:42:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is ordering a second hot fudge sundae?\NThe child is.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.61,0:43:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is having a second helping of potatoes and gravy?\NThe child is.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.12,0:43:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And after we indulge the child then,\Nwithout realizing this is what is going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.12,0:43:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and after the meal is over,\Nwhat happens now is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.22,0:43:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the child leaves.\NI mean, he has had his fill.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.22,0:43:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And who takes his place?\NThe parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.22,0:43:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The parent says,\Nhow could you have been so stupid?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.22,0:43:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you have seconds?\NWhy did you add a piece of pie?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.22,0:43:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you put ice cream on top of the pie?\NI mean, think of the calories.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.22,0:43:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You are really stupid.\NYou are really weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.22,0:43:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have any willpower.\NYou are no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.22,0:43:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Your self-worth is rotten.\NSo, now what happens is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.22,0:43:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you are subjected to the angry parent blaming you.\NBlaming who?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.96,0:43:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Blaming the child.\NWhere has the adult been all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.96,0:43:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He has been out to lunch.\NHe wasn't there at meal time
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.96,0:43:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and he isn't there after meal time.\NThe child and the parent have taken over the whole eating program.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.96,0:43:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And isn't that natural?\NBecause where did these eating patterns set up in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.96,0:44:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They set up with the child.\NAnd who is sitting next to the child but the parent?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.96,0:44:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the child and the parent tapes have been\Nwhat has been running the whole eating pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.37,0:44:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The adult hasn't had a chance.\NNow, the way to counteract this then
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.56,0:44:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be aware that this pattern is running.\NJust to be aware of it already begins to change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.56,0:44:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you make a note to yourself.\NYou can put it on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.56,0:44:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can put it on the refrigerator\Nand call forth consciously your adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.56,0:44:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I tell my child,\Nlook, you are going to be handled.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.56,0:44:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a place for an adult now\Nbecause my adult is very conscious of his eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.56,0:44:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My adult knows about calories.\NMy adult knows all these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.56,0:44:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I consciously call forth my adult\Nto be there at the meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.56,0:44:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I consciously summon him forth.\NI say, you know, the adult me is here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.98,0:44:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I consciously reject the presence of the child.\NNow because the overindulgence doesn't happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.98,0:45:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,when the meal is over, my adult stays there.\NNo parent comes in to blame me for what's been done
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.98,0:45:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because no crime has been committed.\NThe crime is not committed by the adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.98,0:45:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the crime is committed by the child.\NSo allowing ourselves then to go unconscious when we eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.08,0:45:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't mean unconscious like pass out.\NYou know, that's not what we're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.08,0:45:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about that aspect of our personality\Nthat comes forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.08,0:45:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not aware that it's the child now\Ncoming in to take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.08,0:45:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the child doesn't care about weight.\NThe child doesn't care about having a good figure.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.08,0:45:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,These are not things that bother a child.\NThese are not things that bother the parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.88,0:45:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want the adult to take over\Nthe actual experience of eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.88,0:45:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the child and not the angry punitive parent.\NWe don't want to be at the effect of either one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.88,0:45:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is no place now for the child\Nbecause he has no self-control
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.88,0:46:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and no intelligence about such matters.\NAnd we don't want the parent there
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.88,0:46:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because the parent is into the no, no, no\Nand the self-blame and the self-hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.91,0:46:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's get rid of them at meal time.\NWe send the child out to play
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.91,0:46:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll tell the parent to go take a nap\Nand we'll tell them it's time for the adult
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.91,0:46:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to come forth now.\NThese you'll find work extremely well.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.32,0:46:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, it doesn't take willpower.\NIt doesn't take self-control.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.32,0:46:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't take resisting anything.\NIt just takes being aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.32,0:46:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Be aware.\NSo you sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.32,0:46:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You say hello to your adult, you see.\NAnd when you sit down to eat, be conscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.32,0:46:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I've watched myself do this.\NJust as you sit down at the dinner table,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.42,0:46:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you watch the kid come up in you.\NOh, look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.42,0:46:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that that's there at the table?\NOh, wow, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.42,0:46:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the pile of mashed potatoes.\NLook at the gravy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.42,0:46:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you watch people's face when they sit down at the table\Nand you'll see who's up in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.42,0:47:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the eyes pop open.\NYou watch the pupils go like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.42,0:47:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If that isn't a five-year-old kid, I never saw one.\NSo you see a businessman, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.42,0:47:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and he walks into the restaurant\Nand he's got his briefcase and he's so serious
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.42,0:47:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and he goes down to the cafeteria line\Nand he sits down.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.42,0:47:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch his face now as he puts his napkin in front of him.\NHe picks up his napkin.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.42,0:47:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes,\NSomebody else is there already, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.48,0:47:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the kid all ready to have a good time.\NAnd, of course, after he leaves,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.48,0:47:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,he gets up, he folds his paper,\Nand now you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.68,0:47:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I ate too much.\NInstantly, now who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.68,0:47:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the frown and the...\NHe's already berating himself
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.28,0:47:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,as he walks out of the restaurant.\NHe's counting all the calories in his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.28,0:47:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He just ate 3,850 calories for dinner.\NAnd his doctor told him he's only supposed to eat 900 calories a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.28,0:47:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He figures he can't eat till next Tuesday now.\NAnd how is he going to survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.28,0:47:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So how to break out of this self-defeating pattern\Njust by being aware?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.28,0:48:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, make a little sign for yourself that says,\NHello, adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.41,0:48:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Be conscious. Beware.\NYou'll find that the adult enjoys eating a great deal too.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.41,0:48:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He just doesn't go crazy so easily, you know.\NI forgot to mention something before
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.01,0:48:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was talking about avoiding eating a lot of sugar and sweets\Non an empty stomach,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.01,0:48:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and I want to mention it so that I don't forget it.\NAnd that is we want to avoid fluctuating blood sugar
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.27,0:48:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,as much as possible when we're first initiating this program.\NBecause in the unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.27,0:48:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a drop in blood sugar is often associated in the mind\Nwith hunger and hungry feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.27,0:48:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we, on an empty stomach for instance,\Neat a hot fudge sundae,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.27,0:48:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,then you'll watch the blood sugar shoots up like this\Nand then adrenaline is poured out
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.27,0:49:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and insulin is poured out\Nand you'll see what happens is the blood sugar then
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.46,0:49:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to drop rapidly.\NBehaviorally, in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.46,0:49:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we have associated that then with feeling hungry.\NYou see, we're not actually hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.46,0:49:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Our stomach is still full.\NWe have more calories in us than what we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.46,0:49:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's the rapidity and the degree of drop of this blood sugar\Nfrom where it started previously
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.46,0:49:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,then triggers the sensation of hunger again.\NIt's much easier when you're initiating this program
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.52,0:49:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and stay on a high protein or a high fat diet\Nbecause then your blood sugar tends to stay somewhat level.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.52,0:49:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't hit those sudden drops.\NThey give you that feeling that you want to eat something right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.52,0:49:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore it makes it a little easier on yourself.\NThe point is we want to avoid suffering in all its forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.59,0:49:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want to experience suffering in any kind of a program\Nbecause otherwise it's not going to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.59,0:49:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Counting calories and depriving yourself\Nis setting up a form of suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.59,0:50:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happens then is the unconscious guilt gets satisfied.\NYou see, the overindulgence sets up guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.62,0:50:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we diet and that is sort of like self-punitive.\NYou sort of punish yourself by going on bread and water
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.68,0:50:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,like a prisoner for a certain period of time.\NThen after we've punished ourselves sufficiently
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.84,0:50:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,for all this overindulgence in the past\Nwhat happens now is the guilt disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.84,0:50:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And once the guilt disappears\Nthen the old eating habit pattern returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.84,0:50:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So that overindulgence, feeling guilty, going into a self-punitive\Nyou know, bread and water kind of diet, going to that extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.39,0:50:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to get off that imbalance of extremes.\NFirst swinging to the overeating and overindulgence
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.39,0:50:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,then swinging into the guilt and the self-punitive deprivation.\NDeprivation is not the way to happiness, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.39,0:50:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor is overindulgence.\NBut transcending it and being in the middle of the two
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.39,0:51:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you're over and above the problem.\NSo that the adult is there to take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.39,0:51:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Using consciousness techniques, making it easy, making it enjoyable.\NIt's really delightful to realize that you have just handled that and transcended it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.42,0:51:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that's plagued you your whole lifetime can be handled\Nyou know, in a matter of minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.52,0:51:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The first day, I think the first day I tried this\NI don't think I spent over a total of 45 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.52,0:51:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting down handling those sensations.\NAnd the second day maybe 20 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.52,0:51:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The third day maybe 10 minutes.\NAnd the next day maybe 4 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.68,0:51:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And since that time I don't think I've spent collectively an hour\Nin the last 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.68,0:51:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Collectively over a 10 year period I don't think I've even spent.\NYou see, if you take a stopwatch and start.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.68,0:51:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You start to feel hungry, you start a stopwatch.\NAnd then you sit down and you use this technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.68,0:51:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the hunger feeling is gone you hit the stopwatch again.\NIf you did that I don't think you would even collect an hour
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.68,0:52:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,over a 10 year period of time.\NSo that certainly is not much in the way of effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.68,0:52:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Not much in the way of suffering.\NNo willpower is involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.68,0:52:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of willpower what we're using instead is willingness.\NSee, willingness is a positive energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.68,0:52:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's powerful at 310.\NAnd using willpower, resisting.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.71,0:52:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Willpower means I will resist this.\NIs a negative energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.71,0:52:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has a weak power of only 125.\NSo instead we're going to be using willingness, acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.71,0:52:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to be happy about it.\NIf your willpower is at about 300,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.71,0:52:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say it's at about 500,\Nwe're going to end up joyful and feeling great about ourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.71,0:52:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Feeling wonderful about ourself.\NAnd of course the body begins to feel wonderful about itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.71,0:52:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we begin to experience our body in sort of a happy way.\NA happy way.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.48,0:52:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Another way to increase the rapidity of the effect of this\Nis by watching your activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.48,0:53:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,See, we said exercise is great.\NBut if you're going to set about taking off weight through exercise,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.48,0:53:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How many mornings are you going to get up and do calisthenics, you see?\NNo matter how attractive the person is on the television set,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.48,0:53:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you're just going to do this a number of times,\Nand the enthusiasm by the fourth day wears out,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.48,0:53:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and before you know it, you're back into the same old pattern.\NExercise is wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.57,0:53:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good for that sense of well-being.\NBut as weight reduction folks, we all know the truth of that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.86,0:53:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It works so well, actually,\Nthat you may end up having a problem of being thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.31,0:53:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what happened with me.\NThis worked so well that pretty soon the appetite disappeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.53,0:53:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the hunger disappeared, all these cycles of eating, indulgence,\Nand then feeling guilty disappeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.53,0:53:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and I noticed that I would forget to eat.\NForgot to eat breakfast, forgot to eat lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.53,0:53:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I would get busy with the activities of the day\Nand totally forget eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.53,0:54:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in a while it would come to you in the beginning\Nbecause it's a habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.60,0:54:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's meal time.\NAnd then what you do is you sit down
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.66,0:54:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and you let go resisting that the same as you did the sensations.\NAnd you'll notice that the idea that I must eat breakfast,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.66,0:54:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I must eat lunch, I must eat dinner,\Nthese are cultural conditionings.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.66,0:54:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't have any reality to them.\NIt's just as easy to not eat all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.66,0:54:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've actually gone days without eating\Nand didn't even notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.98,0:54:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,One time I went from Monday to Thursday.\NI was so busy with activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.98,0:54:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And on Thursday I suddenly realized\NI don't think I've eaten the last couple of days.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.17,0:54:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And sure enough I hadn't.\NAnd the family began to complain that I was too thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.56,0:54:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I had to consciously be aware that it's necessary to eat\Nand sort of reprogram myself a little bit back into eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.56,0:54:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So it works extremely well.\NIt brings a great deal of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.56,0:55:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And we might talk about something else too.\NWe might talk about using another consciousness technique
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.07,0:55:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which has a general application.\NAll the things we're talking about today,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.07,0:55:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it of course will dawn on you,\Nhave many applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.90,0:55:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a technique also\Nwhere you picture the kind of body you want to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.90,0:55:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NYou picture the kind of body you want to have
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.96,0:55:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and you picture the kind of feeling\Nthat you want to have about having this kind of a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.83,0:55:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember some time in your life\Nwhen you were feeling joyful and pleased with yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.83,0:55:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And now picture yourself,\Npicture that body the way you want it to be
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.21,0:55:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and reawaken that emotion.\NPicture yourself as, let's say you want to be slim,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.47,0:55:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,picture yourself as slim\Nand begin to love that picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.47,0:55:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Love that picture of yourself.\NLove that picture of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.47,0:55:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And now let it go.\NNow let it go knowing that that,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.47,0:56:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,what you've done is you've set up a program,\Nyou've set up what is going to be in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.47,0:56:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the mind will now begin\Nto move in that direction automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.47,0:56:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Just love that picture of yourself\Nand if you like you can put the number of pounds under it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.53,0:56:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now I have 132 under my picture.\NSo I picture how I want to look.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.53,0:56:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, relatively slim so your clothes feel comfortable.\NAnd under that I have a picture of 132.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.53,0:56:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just love that about myself\Nand I say, you know, fantastic at your age to be slim
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.53,0:56:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and active and feel good about the body.\NI love myself for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.65,0:56:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we want to stop identifying with the body.\NYou know, I am not the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.65,0:56:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a body.\NSo how I view my relationship to body,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.65,0:56:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes important.\NI am that which has a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.65,0:56:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I am that which has a car.\NI am that which has a house I live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.65,0:57:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So the car, the house, I mean the car,\Nthe body becomes like those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.65,0:57:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes like my pet.\NIt becomes like my pet animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.65,0:57:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,My friend, Gloria Ross, calls it her pet.\NAnd that is a great way to look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.65,0:57:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,See, this is my little pet.\NThis is my bicycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.65,0:57:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my vehicle.\NThis is my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.65,0:57:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my pet that carries me around.\NBut you see, it is different than saying I am that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.65,0:57:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I am that.\NBecause if I say I am the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.65,0:57:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then I am subject to what goes on with the body.\NAnd if it gains weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.65,0:57:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then it is me that is fat.\NI am the one at fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.65,0:57:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I berate me thinking I am the body.\NIt doesn't take too much in the way of meditative self-awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.10,0:57:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize that you are that which experiences the body.\NYou are not the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.10,0:57:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Right in the beginning we said that\Nbody cannot experience itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.58,0:57:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It only can be experienced in mind.\NMind can only be experienced by consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.58,0:58:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness itself can only be experienced by\Na field greater than itself called awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.64,0:58:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So I am that which is aware of the body.\NI am that which is beyond the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.12,0:58:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So how I am with that body now?\NI am one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.12,0:58:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The body is another.\NAnd this body is going to reflect
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.12,0:58:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what I am holding in consciousness.\NSo that my problem is not the body at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.12,0:58:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is what I am holding in consciousness.\NMy problem is merely to change the vibrational body.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.12,0:58:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,To change the vibrational patterns within consciousness.\NAnd this body is going to do automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.12,0:58:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is told to do.\NThe body can't think.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.12,0:58:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The body has no mind.\NWhat I am, that which I am, has the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.12,0:58:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And the body follows what I tell it to do.\NSo this imaging technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.12,0:58:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the way in which I hold as pleasurable my relationship,\Nand I enjoy its activity now.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.12,0:59:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I enjoy the way it sort of bounces around.\NIt sort of does its...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.12,0:59:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, as we keep letting go\Nand keep following these techniques,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.12,0:59:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is the body seems to get lighter.\NThe body, having nothing to do with weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.12,0:59:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is experienced as progressively weightless.\NAnd as we move up the scale of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.12,0:59:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,after a while we are hardly aware that the body even exists.\NLet's look at the scale of consciousness then
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.96,0:59:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in a different way.\NLet's look at
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.40,0:59:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,how we are with our weight problem.\NHow am I holding this problem
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.50,0:59:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I can get out of the emotional destructive patterns\Nwhich have accompanied it?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.50,0:59:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's generally thought that these negative feelings\Nare the cause of the weight problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.50,0:59:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look into it, you'll see this is really not so.\NYou'll see that these are the reactions to the weight problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.17,0:59:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the reactions to the weight problem.\NAnd sometimes they are the corollary
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.17,1:00:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,or the parallel.\NLet's look and see how we've been holding
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.16,1:00:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the weight problem up to this point.\NMost of us have been down here at the bottom of the box
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.16,1:00:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,called guilt.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.16,1:00:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt is an energy field of 30.\NIt's very weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.29,1:00:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If you try to handle your weight problem\Nor any problem, alcohol, relationships,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.29,1:00:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,if you try to handle anything from the level of guilt,\Nyou can see how much energy you've got to work with.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.29,1:00:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got like 30 bucks as compared to love,\Nwhich is 500 bucks.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.29,1:00:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,30 bucks isn't going to buy you much progress in anything.\NNot only that, but the energy field is negative,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.29,1:00:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning you're going to feel lousy about the whole thing.\NYou're going to be full of self-hatred,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.29,1:00:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and actually the process is destructive.\NThe process is destructive.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.29,1:00:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, people have actually committed suicide\Nover their weight problem, their self-indulgence.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.29,1:01:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you don't handle it from guilt,\Nyou move up to hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.29,1:01:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This state here, which has an energy field of 50,\Nis accompanied by hopelessness and despair.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.29,1:01:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This means my case is hopeless.\NI've tried all the diets.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.29,1:01:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I've tried the milk farms, all that.\NI've lost the energy with which to even address this problem anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.29,1:01:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the victim of it, and I just surrender to it and give up.\NSo this is, I am hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.29,1:01:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The next one above it is grief.\NThis is the depression.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.29,1:01:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the depression about the problem,\Nthe regret, feeling despondent and dispirited.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.29,1:01:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NOr the fear of this problem and its consequences.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.36,1:01:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all negative feelings.\NYou see the direction of the arrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.36,1:01:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That I'm going to die of a heart attack.\NThis overweight is going to kill me, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.36,1:01:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This is full of worry, anxiety, and panic.\NIt's going to destroy my relationships and my future.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.36,1:01:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, your self-esteem is deflated.\NSo people with a weight problem often socially withdraw.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.36,1:01:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They compensate.\NThey compensate in other ways,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.36,1:02:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because they feel inadequate due to this energy field.\NThey're not inadequate people at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.36,1:02:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that they're holding that about their situation,\Nand then the negativity of it affects their emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.80,1:02:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already talked about this level here.\NYou know, the desiring, the wanting, the craving,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.80,1:02:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,behind all this, the entrapment.\NAnd we move up to the next field, which is anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.80,1:02:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the person is angry about their weight problem.\NThey resent it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.80,1:02:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They're full of grievances about it.\NAnd although 150 is more effective,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.80,1:02:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you're probably going to be more effective utilizing anger,\Ncertainly, than guilt or hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.80,1:02:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're angry enough about your weight problem,\Nyou can move up to pride, which is 175.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.80,1:02:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough to run the United States Marine Corps, pride.\NThat's a lot of power.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.80,1:02:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And try to move through pride,\Nbecause that's not exactly a great place to hang out in,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.12,1:02:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the inflation of the ego that happens there,\Nand move up to courage.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.12,1:03:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The courage, now that you know some tools that are really going to work,\Nthe courage to try them out.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.12,1:03:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 200.\N200 is a lot of power as compared to 30 or 50.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.12,1:03:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It enables you to face, to cope, to handle.\NAnd what happens there is you become empowered.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.12,1:03:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You now become empowered.\NThe truth of it is you haven't known how to handle it up to now,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.12,1:03:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or you would have.\NIsn't that so?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.12,1:03:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If you really knew how to handle it, you would have.\NThat's the truth of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.12,1:03:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You use these releasing techniques, this letting go,\Nthese letting go techniques,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.76,1:03:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and you become detached from the whole problem.\NIf the weight stays, it stays,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.02,1:03:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and if it doesn't stay, it doesn't make any difference.\NAt this point, you say, it's not apathy, it's not hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.02,1:03:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, you're released from the thing,\Nand therefore, you're feeling good,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.02,1:03:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and you move up to a willingness.\NWillingness at 310 is a lot of energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.02,1:03:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Compare it to guilt.\NCompare it to grief.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.02,1:04:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Compare it to...\NYou see how much power you've got now,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.02,1:04:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and here you're in agreement.\NYou're aligned with this technique.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.02,1:04:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Your intention is finally up,\Nthat you're finally going to handle it,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.02,1:04:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and you accept that it can be handled,\Nthat you're an adequate person.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.02,1:04:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You start becoming confident,\Nand there's a transformation now occurring
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.02,1:04:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because you realize the power to handle this is within you,\Nand you start moving up into a lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.05,1:04:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire to really love yourself,\Nto love this body,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.05,1:04:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,now that you don't identify with it as me.\NThis body is not me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.05,1:04:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take off my left leg, I'm still me.\NIf you take off my right leg, I'm still me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.05,1:04:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Take off the left arm, I'm still me.\NTake off the right arm, I'm still me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.05,1:04:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Take off both ears, I'm still me.\NYou get that the me is me,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.05,1:04:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm not the body.\NSo whether it weighs 200 pounds or 85 pounds,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.05,1:04:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that which I am is unassailed by that,\Nand I must learn to love that body now,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.72,1:05:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to really value it,\Nand see that it's just an enjoyable little puppet.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.98,1:05:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to relate to the body is that it's a happy little puppet.\NYou see, and it goes about its way,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.98,1:05:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and the less attention you pay to it,\Nthe better it really handles itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.98,1:05:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It just does what it's doing automatically.\NAnd you see, if you get to love it, you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.98,1:05:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,your brain begins to release endorphins.\NEndorphins.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.98,1:05:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When endorphins are released,\Na process goes on in consciousness called revelation.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.98,1:05:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to see things differently.\NWhat do you see differently?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.98,1:05:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how wonderful your little body is.\NThat's one of the things you begin to see.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.98,1:05:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to love it and get a kick out of it.\NWhen you're overweight, are you getting a kick out of your body?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.98,1:05:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you don't get a kick out of it.\NEvery time you look at it, it throws you back into guilt again.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.98,1:05:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Up here, you start getting a kick out of it.\NYou start getting playful with it, sort of a joyfulness.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.52,1:05:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, a joyfulness and a happiness about this little body.\NIt bounces around and you're just sort of dimly aware of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.52,1:06:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you're experiencing your existence\Nfrom a position of allness.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.94,1:06:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NOnce you become conscious about where experience is happening,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.97,1:06:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you get that experiencing is happening everywhere.\NYou begin to identify with everywhere-ness.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.97,1:06:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of stomach-ness or bulge-ness or ulcer-ness,\Nall those localized things,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.97,1:06:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that which I am is a conscious being.\NConsciousness is everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.97,1:06:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I begin to experience my existence\Nas being almost everywhere in space.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.04,1:06:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And within this everywhere-ness, within this allness,\Nthis happy little puppet bounces around.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.04,1:06:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how it just does what it does.\NAnd it has a good time doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.32,1:06:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We start to come from the heart about it then.\NHeart with a capital H.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.32,1:07:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Heart not meaning the physical organ.\NHeart meaning that quality of valuing your existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.60,1:07:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming from that greatness.\NComing from the big-ness.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.60,1:07:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming from the joy of aliveness.\NAnd seeing the body as a contributor to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.60,1:07:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As something that's enjoyable.\NAs something that you can have fun with.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.60,1:07:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Something you can experiment.\NSomething you can play with.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.37,1:07:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This talk today gives you something\Nto have a good time with.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.37,1:07:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really fun to sit down and watch this phenomenon happen.\NIt's really joyful.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.56,1:07:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really fun.\NYou know, within a day or two,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.82,1:07:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,within a day or two, it's all over.\NWithin a couple of days, once you're released off
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.95,1:07:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,this appetite-hunger cycle,\Nthe rest of it is automatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.95,1:07:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you don't have to do another thing.\NIf you want to throw in some common sense
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.49,1:07:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and have a diet soda, you know,\Nhave a diet Coke instead of a regular Coke,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.49,1:07:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and save yourself 100 calories,\Nwell, that's common sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.49,1:08:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's up to you.\NThat's different than being at the effect of.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.49,1:08:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's different than being run by.\NIt's different than being run by the guilt of.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.49,1:08:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's considerably different,\Nbecause now you're at choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.56,1:08:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So if my weight gets a little on the high side,\Nanother trick that works is never to allow yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.00,1:08:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to go over a certain number of pounds.\NIf I pick 132, that means that by accident
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.00,1:08:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it runs to 134.\NThen I go back to this technique again
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.20,1:08:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and get off that cycle,\Nbecause those old patterns can tend to recur,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.20,1:08:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but they're very easy to let go of once it recurs.\NYou can really do it once or twice.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.20,1:08:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time you feel hungry, you sit down and you skip it.\NYou skip the eating until that hunger disappears.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.84,1:08:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you can go out in the refrigerator if you want.\NAnd don't forget to have your adult at the refrigerator.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.84,1:08:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Put a note inside your refrigerator when you open it,\Nmaybe a picture of yourself as you as an adult, you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.84,1:08:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you realize you've got a choice\Nof whose arm is going to be reaching into the refrigerator.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.84,1:09:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep that kid out, you know,\Nbecause the kid is going to help himself in the refrigerator.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.84,1:09:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And let your adult be there.\NSo the whole thing becomes a very enjoyable experience,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.93,1:09:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,one in which you truly begin to love yourself.\NThe basis of all these self-healing techniques
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.93,1:09:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that we talk about are merely ways of loving yourself,\Nways of really beginning to value yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.93,1:09:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Really ways of loving that which you are,\Nthat which you really are in truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.93,1:09:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which you are in truth then looks at the body,\Nthat which you really are looks now at your little body
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.38,1:09:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and begins to get a kick out of it.\NIt says, gee, I'm having a good time with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.38,1:09:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a fun thing.\NYou begin to see that it really runs almost on automatic all by itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.38,1:09:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see that the mind, the ego,\Nhas played a trick on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.18,1:10:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You think that you make a decision\Nand then the body does that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.18,1:10:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, actually it's doing it by itself.\NIt's on automatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.18,1:10:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've released it out of a negative pattern,\Nthe body will just handle itself very well.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.18,1:10:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We know this with scientific experiments with young children,\Nthat if you allow them to spontaneously select their diet,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.28,1:10:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they will automatically select a balanced diet.\NSo you begin to get a return of faith in nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.28,1:10:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You allow your mind, you allow the body now to sort of be itself.\NThe nature, the nature,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.28,1:10:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is natural within the body itself\Nwill automatically handle its nutritional needs.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.28,1:10:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we get off the social programming,\Nthen that which is automatically self-healing
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.82,1:10:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and healthy within the body takes over.\NIt takes over and it looks after itself
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.82,1:10:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and it chooses what it needs to eat and what it wants to eat\Nand it does extremely well.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.82,1:11:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,My body eats lots of cholesterol\Nand it loves cheese and eggs
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.65,1:11:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and it would make any dietician faint,\Nany nutritionist I'm sure would faint
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.65,1:11:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,when they see what I have for breakfast.\NAnd yet the cholesterol is normal,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.65,1:11:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the blood sugar is normal,\Nall the blood chemistries are normal.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.68,1:11:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a faith then, you might say,\Nin the God within nature itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.68,1:11:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The God within nature itself.\NThe body being part of nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.68,1:11:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The body being part.\NOf the beautiful nature of this planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.68,1:11:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It has its own inner wisdom\Nand when we remove the artificial conditioning of our society,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.68,1:11:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,its own innate inner wisdom comes forth\Nand it expresses itself in a sense of aliveness,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.68,1:11:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a sense of joyfulness, a sense of lightness,\Nthe capacity to feel good at all times
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.38,1:11:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll see that its weight handles itself automatically.\NTo do this then all we're asking for
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.48,1:12:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is really a few minutes of time\Nwith many years of joyful reward coming as a result.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.48,1:12:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a good time with this little body.\NLove it. Be good to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.48,1:12:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiss it.\NGive it all the love and attention that it needs.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.48,1:12:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that it belongs to you\Nbut it is not what you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.48,1:12:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not you but it belongs to you.\NIt's a lovely possession.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.48,1:12:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy it while you've got it.\NWhy not have a good time with it?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.54,1:12:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Take it out of the category of pain,\Nsin, suffering and guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.54,1:12:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Give that up forever.\NChoose joy as your way of being with it
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.54,1:12:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and have a good time.
